description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a confident diabetes specialist dietitian to work in a busy tertiary outpatient service, covering maternity leave until &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;July 2021&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The primary area of work is in antenatal diabetes, where the dietitian plays a crucial role in the clinical outcomes of pregnant women and their children. You will work closely with the medical and nursing professionals in the team, in this busy face to face clinical setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;During this period, some of the work supporting diabetes patients (outside of the antenatal service) is being delivered through telemedicine, utilising the technologies that exist to support patients already such as continuous glucose monitors, to keep people safe and out of hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are able to demonstrate your ability to deliver an evidence based dietetic service in complex Type 1 and other insulin dependent diabetes care, as well as show an innovative approach to managing patient care during this uncertain time, we welcome your application. &lt;span&gt;Experience with Freestyle Libré and insulin pumps is important.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sinead Burke&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead Dietitian, Renal and Diabetes Therapy Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: sinead.burke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 020 7830 2616 or extension 31739&lt;/p&gt;
